  "description": [
    "6 TuWy January 21 IW SENTINEL COUNT More Drivers On Road By United Press International DETROIT Even though automobile production fell off 16 per cent in 1961 ownership and use of motor vehicles reached an alltime high the Automobile Manufacturers Association reports Passenger car registration climbed 18 million to 635 million and there were 125 million trucks and buses on streets and highways Households with two or more cars increased from 41 million to 74 million The number of licensed drivers has increased in ten years from 64 million to 90 millions The average car now is driven 10000 miles a year and annual consumption of gasoline is about 58 billion gallons Special taxes paid by motorists mounted to 507 bil lion in 1961 or 26 per cent of all state tax revenues This compares with 398 billion in 1956 The Auto Manufacturers Association pointed out that about onethird of the countrys new 41000 mile superhigh way system has been completed r ii M M HELPING HAND When theres illness you think of your doctor first Our registered pharmacists are ready to com pound accurately his every pre scription ready to lend a help ing hand when you need it"
